        <body>       
                
                <pb n="1"/>
            <p>Johns Hopkins University&#44;<lb/>
                Baltimore.<lb/></p>
            <p>Feb. 19&#47;87<lb/></p>
            <p>Dear Mr. Morais<lb/></p>
            <p>I received yours of 19<hi rend="sup">th</hi> &#38;<lb/> was glad to hear of the action<lb/> of the Trustees in placing the tuition of<lb/> the Seminary on a regular footing.  I<lb/> do not consider your visits to<lb/> New York as a waste however<lb/> the more the boys know you the<lb/> better for them.  Should I hear<lb/> anything of interest concerning the<lb/> Landro family I will certainly leave<lb/> you know.  You will be<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="2"/>
            <p>glad to hear I am <sic>shure</sic> that<lb/> I completed my examinations successfully<lb/> on <del>Tuesday</del> Friday that my thesis<lb/> has been accepted &#38; that I will<lb/> receive a Ph. D. degree next Tuesday<lb/> an end impossible but for the<lb/> help which you have given me<lb/> from boyhood up and which I never<lb/> think of but with gratitude.  Please<lb/> remember me to your family &#38;<lb/> believe me<lb/> very truly yours<lb/> Cyrus Adler<lb/></p>
                
            <p>Did you ever know a Samuel<lb/> Binion who studied with Luzzatto&#63;<lb/></p>
            </body>
    </text>
